On 29 Jan 2002, CG wrote:

> Ok - so you're talking about the black, thick, hard phenolic-looking
> 'standoffs' - bout 1/4" thick.

Check... correct!

>
> I didn't install these when i buttoned up my solid lift 1800 with the 2bbl
> weber.

And you should not have with that carb/intake... the thin metal gaskets
pass heat from the head to the intake  manifold, the phenolic  do not (as
much).  With the unheated  runners you have, you want as much heat as you
can get to get to the runners (won't help much, but may help some with
carb icing)


